ABUJA – The Northeast Zone of the All Progressives Congress (APC) has named a 39-member Central Steering Committee to oversee affairs of the party in Adamawa State and reposition it for victory, while also working with its National Working Committee (NWC). The committee headed by Abdulrahman Adamu has Secretary to the Government of the Federation (SGF), Boss Mustapha, and Mohammed Bello, Minister of FCT as co-chairmen. Among a robust term of reference given the committee was a charge to reconcile all aggrieved aspirants/candidates that vied for positions during the 2019 general election. The Adamawa APC has been in crisis following the victory of the opposition Peoples Democratic Party (PDP) in the state. The PDP’s victory was linked to internal crisis that polarised APC members during the election. The committee is also charged with the task of developing programme of action to reposition and strengthen APC in Adamawa, as well as propose modalities to ensure free and fair primaries ahead of the coming local government area election and future election in the state. The committee is also to propose ways and means of raising funds for running the affairs of the party In Adamawa State. It is also saddled with the task of developing effective media and public enlightenment programme for repositioning the party back to winning ways in the state, among others. Other members of the committee include immediate past Governor Mohammed Umaru Jibrilla Bindow, Mallam Nuhu Ribadu, Dahiru Bobbo, Jonathan Silas Zwingina and Ahmed Hassan Barata, among many others.